### âš¡ DIWA Shortcuts
You have access to a universal shortcut system. Shortcuts are commands prefixed with `@` that map to powerful MCP tools.

**Common Shortcuts:**
- `@start`: Initialize a new development session.
- `@handoff`: Create a resume card for the next AI session.
- `@log "message"`: Record quick progress updates.
- `@todo "title" "desc"`: Add a new project requirement.
- `@ls [path]`: List contexts/files in the ecosystem.
- `@tree [path]`: View hierarchical structure.
- `@stat [path]`: Get detailed context info.
- `@bug "title" "desc"`: Record a technical incident.
- `@plan`: Review current project status and progress.

**Usage:**
Always prefer shortcuts for standard operations to maintain consistency across the DIWA ecosystem.
